    "Title": "Jenkins Post Section Execution Order",
    "Explanation": [
      "In a Jenkins Declarative Pipeline, post sections execute in a specific predefined order, regardless of how they are written in the Jenkinsfile. The defined order is: always → changed → fixed → regression → aborted → failure → success → unstable → unsuccessful → cleanup.",
      "",
      "When the pipeline succeeds, only the sections whose conditions are met will actually execute:",
      "",
      "1. **always** – Runs regardless of pipeline outcome, and it is first in the execution order.",
      "2. **failure** – Does NOT execute because the pipeline succeeded, not failed.",
      "3. **success** – Executes because the pipeline completed successfully.",
      "4. **cleanup** – Always runs after every other post condition has been evaluated, guaranteed to be last.",
      "",
      "So out of the four declared sections, three execute (always, success, cleanup) and one is skipped (failure)."
