      "",
      "1. **maxUnavailable: 0** means the number of available (Ready) Pods must never drop below the desired replica count of 6. Zero unavailability is guaranteed at all times.",
      "2. **maxSurge: 1** means the total number of Pods (old + new) can exceed the desired count by at most 1, allowing up to 7 Pods simultaneously.",
      "",
      "The update proceeds like this:",
      "- Start: 6 old Pods, all Ready (available = 6).",
      "- Step 1: 1 new Pod is created (total = 7). The new Pod is not yet Ready, so available = 6 (all old). No old Pod can be terminated yet because that would drop available below 6.",
      "- Step 2: The new Pod becomes Ready. Now available = 7 (6 old + 1 new). Since available (7) \u003e desired (6), one old Pod can now be safely terminated without violating the maxUnavailable: 0 constraint.",
      "- This cycle repeats one Pod at a time until all old Pods are replaced.",
      "",
      "Therefore, exactly 1 new-version Pod must be Ready before the first old-version Pod is terminated."
