      "",
      "1. **maxUnavailable: 0** means all 6 replicas must remain available at all times during the update. No old Pod can be terminated until there's a ready replacement.",
      "",
      "2. **maxSurge: 1** means the Deployment can temporarily scale up to 7 Pods maximum (6 desired + 1 surge).",
      "",
      "The rolling update process works as follows:",
      "- Initial state: 6 old Pods (all Ready)",
      "- Step 1: Create 1 new Pod (now 7 total: 6 old + 1 new pending)",
      "- Step 2: Wait for the new Pod to become Ready",
      "- Step 3: Once the new Pod is Ready (7 Ready Pods: 6 old + 1 new), one old Pod can be terminated while maintaining 6 available Pods (5 old + 1 new)",
      "- This process repeats one Pod at a time",
      "",
      "Since maxUnavailable is 0, the cluster must always maintain 6 Ready Pods. The only way to terminate an old Pod while keeping 6 available is to first have a new Pod Ready. With maxSurge of 1, only one new Pod can be created at a time before an old one is removed.",
      "",
      "Therefore, exactly 1 new-version Pod must be Ready before the first old-version Pod can be terminated."
    ],
